\exercice*
Construire sur la figure ci-dessous les points $C$, $D$, $E$, $F$ et $G$ pour obtenir un zigzag tel que :\par
$\widehat{ABC}=\ang{24} \qquad \widehat{BCD}=\ang{50} \qquad \widehat{CDE}=\ang{117} \qquad \widehat{DEF}=\ang{163} \qquad \widehat{EFG}=\ang{122} \qquad $\par
Quand le travail est fait avec une bonne précision, les 
droites $(AF)$ et $(BG)$ se coupent au c\oe ur de la cible.
\begin{center}\fbox{
\begin{tikzpicture}[ultra thick, scale=1.1]
\coordinate (A) at (0.2, 0.2);
\coordinate (B) at (0.47902589497650183, 4.190256201039297);
\coordinate (C) at (1.8471064682791771, 0.4314857178956637);
\coordinate (D) at (3.8471064682791773, 3.895587333033418);
\coordinate (E) at (7.841624607297472, 3.6862435080616427);
\coordinate (F) at (11.722807512401458, 4.653931090460314);
\coordinate (G) at (14.600166713756062, 1.875297608624325);
\draw (A) node[below]{$A$};
\draw (B) node[above]{$B$};
\draw[Maroon] (A) -- (B);
\draw[Maroon,draw,decoration={markings, mark=at position .5  with {\node[transform shape] {$\parallel$};}}] (A) edge[decorate] (B);\draw[Gray] (7.531947919462909, 3.0340307478872273) circle (0.1);
\draw[Gray] (7.531947919462909, 3.0340307478872273) circle (0.2);
\draw[Gray] (7.531947919462909, 3.0340307478872273) circle (0.3);
\draw[Gray] (7.531947919462909, 3.0340307478872273) circle (0.4);
\draw[dotted, Maroon] (B) -- (G);
\draw[dotted, Maroon] (A) -- (F);
\draw (C) node[below]{$C$};
\draw (D) node[above]{$D$};
\draw (E) node[below]{$E$};
\draw (F) node[above]{$F$};
\draw (G) node[below]{$G$};
\draw[Maroon] (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- (E) -- (F) -- (G);
\draw[Maroon,draw,decoration={markings, mark=at position .5  with {\node[transform shape] {$\parallel$};}}]
    (B) edge[decorate] (C)
    (C) edge[decorate] (D)
    (D) edge[decorate] (E)
    (E) edge[decorate] (F)
    (F) edge[decorate] (G);\draw pic [draw=Maroon,angle radius=20pt, angle eccentricity=2, "\ang{ 24 }"] {angle = A--B--C};
\draw pic [draw=Maroon,angle radius=20pt, angle eccentricity=2, "\ang{ 50 }"] {angle = D--C--B};
\draw pic [draw=Maroon,angle radius=20pt, angle eccentricity=2, "\ang{ 117 }"] {angle = C--D--E};
\draw pic [draw=Maroon,angle radius=20pt, angle eccentricity=2, "\ang{ 163 }"] {angle = F--E--D};
\draw pic [draw=Maroon,angle radius=20pt, angle eccentricity=2, "\ang{ 122 }"] {angle = E--F--G};\end{tikzpicture}
}\end{center}